  <!-- TRIED AND TRIED AGAIN -->
  <div class="section fade-scroll" id="tried">
    <div class="content">
      <h2>â€¢ Introduction / Background of the Study</h2>
      <p>
        This study examines the quarterly examination scores of Grade 10 STE students to identify statistical patterns in their academic performance. According to a 2023 Department of Education (DepEd) report, quarterly exam results are one of the most reliable indicators of student mastery. However, 47% of public school students show inconsistent performance due to factors like study habits and varying teaching strategies.  
        ðŸ”— <a href="https://www.deped.gov.ph" target="_blank">DepEd Official Reports</a>
      </p>
      <p>The goal of this research is to determine whether STE studentsâ€™ performance improves, declines, or remains consistent across all four quarters.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <h2>â€¢ Statement of the Problem</h2>
      <p><strong>Main Problem:</strong> What statistical trends can be observed in the quarterly examination outcomes of Grade 10 STE students?</p>
      <ul>
        <li>1.1 What is the average score for each quarter?</li>
        <li>1.2 Which quarter records the highest and lowest average performance?</li>
        <li>1.3 Are there significant differences between the scores of each quarter?</li>
        <li>1.4 What factors (study habits, subject difficulty) do students believe influence their performance?</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <h2>â€¢ Review of Related Literature</h2>
      <p><strong>1. Academic Performance Trends Across Grading Periods</strong><br>
        Studentsâ€™ scores often fluctuate due to teaching methods and review techniques, with improved performance after targeted intervention.  
        ðŸ”— <a href="https://eric.ed.gov/?id=EJ1254321" target="_blank">Read here</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>2. Study Habits and Academic Achievement</strong><br>
        Consistent daily study habits increase test performance, while cramming is linked to inconsistent results.  
        ðŸ”— <a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Study+Habits+and+Academic+Achievement&hl=en" target="_blank">View study</a>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
